                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[These Signs Show It’s Time to Upgrade Your TV]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/signs-its-time-to-upgrade-your-tv/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/shutterstock_1116120401.jpg" length="385" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Blu-ray]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't settle for a subpar TV experience. Learn the crucial indicators that it's time to invest in a modern television.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>A new television isn't a frequent purchase for most people. Unless you're an AV fanatic (and there's nothing wrong with that!), you're probably not upgrading your TV as often as your smartphone, or your laptop.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/signs-its-time-to-upgrade-your-tv/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Use pandas DataFrames in Python to Analyze and Manipulate Data]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-use-pandas-dataframes-in-python-to-analyze-and-manipulate-data/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[David Delony]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/python-seaborn-logo-chart.jpg" length="915" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Python]]></category><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Understanding your data only needs the right frame of mind.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you want to analyze data in Python, you'll want to become familiar with pandas, as it makes data analysis so much easier. The DataFrame is the primary data format you'll interact with. Here's how to make use of it.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-use-pandas-dataframes-in-python-to-analyze-and-manipulate-data/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Taking a Disney+ Break? Get Your Fix With These Alternatives]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/taking-a-disney-break-get-your-fix-with-these-alternatives/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aran Folsom]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/disney-logo-prominently-centered-with-blurred-movie-and-tv-show-covers-in-the-background.jpg" length="878" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Disney+]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Discover the hidden gems waiting beyond the Disney+ universe on these alternative platforms.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Whether you've had your fill of<a href="https://disneyplus.bn5x.net/c/156932/564546/9358?subId1=UUhtgUeUpU2016899&subId2=ehtg&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.disneyplus.com%2Fhome" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim"> Disney+</a> movies and shows, recently got fed up with <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/disney-and-hulu-are-increasing-their-prices/" target="_blank">rising prices</a>, the politics, or simply want to explore other streaming services, we've got you covered with these alternative platforms that offer similar content that might just satiate you.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 17:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/taking-a-disney-break-get-your-fix-with-these-alternatives/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Add a Website to the Home Screen on iPhone and Android]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/196087/how-to-add-websites-to-the-home-screen-on-any-smartphone-or-tablet/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-app-home-screen.png" length="1880" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cloud & Internet]]></category><category><![CDATA[features]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category><category><![CDATA[ios]]></category><category><![CDATA[Control Panel]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Put websites on your Android or iPhone home screen for quick access.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Your Android phone, iPhone, or iPad home screen isn't just for apps. Whatever device you're using, you can add a website shortcut to the home screen for easy access. In some cases, you can even make the website work like an app.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 17:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/196087/how-to-add-websites-to-the-home-screen-on-any-smartphone-or-tablet/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Can’t Keep Up With Open-Source Software Updates? Here’s How I Do It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/cant-keep-up-with-open-source-software-updates-heres-how-i-do-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/illustration-of-a-windows-11-laptop-and-logos-of-some-open-source-apps-around-it-1.png" length="721" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Not every app or tool has a blog, but most of them have an RSS feed.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>There are many excellent free and open-source software projects, but keeping up with all of them can be difficult, especially when they don’t have blogs or other traditional communication channels. Thankfully, you can still keep track of most software projects in one simple feed, thanks to some hidden features and the magic of RSS.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/cant-keep-up-with-open-source-software-updates-heres-how-i-do-it/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Here's Why MicroSD Cards Disappeared From High-End Phones]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/heres-why-microsd-cards-disappeared-from-high-end-phones/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/illustration_of_microsd_cards_and_a_sim_tray_with_red_x_symbols_over_them.png" length="2567" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[storage]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There were good reasons, for better or worse.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>MicroSD card slots were once ubiquitous on Android phones. Now they’ve all but disappeared—at least from the more premium models. Why are the best phones seemingly making us do with less?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/heres-why-microsd-cards-disappeared-from-high-end-phones/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Let’s Remember Some Weird Phones: The Nextbit Robin]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/remember-some-weird-phones-the-nextbit-robin/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/weird-phones-robin.jpg" length="306" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[HTC]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A phone that truly tried to live in the cloud.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Smartphones today are, frankly, pretty boring—but it wasn’t always this way! Back in 2016, a company called Nextbit had the crazy idea to launch an Android phone that relied almost entirely on cloud storage. It was weird.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/remember-some-weird-phones-the-nextbit-robin/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Matthew McConaughey Takes the Wheel of Apple TV+’s October Lineup]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-on-apple-tv-plus-october-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apple-tv-banner-featuring-ruth-wilson-in-down-cemetery-road-matthew-mcconaughey-in-the-lost-bus-and-jason-clarke-in-the-last-frontier.png" length="1957" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple TV+]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[month]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Apple TV+ has a hefty lineup of entertainment this month in exchange for your full attention.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://shop-links.co/link/?exclusive=1&publisher_slug=howtogeek&u1=UUhtgUeUpU2016854&article_name=Matthew+McConaughey+Takes+the+Wheel+of+Apple+TV%2B%E2%80%99s+October+Lineup&article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fnew-on-apple-tv-plus-october-2025%2F&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftv.apple.com%2F" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Apple TV+</a> adds eight new titles to its queue in October, and all of them are full of plots and dramas you’ll want to see. From a new season of Maya Rudolph's <em>Loot</em> and the premiere of a Jason Clarke-led thriller series to must-see films and documentaries, there’s more than enough to keep you entertained. There's even Matthew McConaughey.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-on-apple-tv-plus-october-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[K-Pop Fans, Don’t Miss These 10 Movies and Shows!]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/best-movies-and-shows-for-fans-of-k-pop/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[T.M. Amrita]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kpop.jpg" length="792" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Netflix]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[KPop Demon Hunters]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Experience the musical glam with these titles. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Beyond the glitz and glam of the K-pop scene, there's a lot to be explored: the underrated B-side tracks, behind-the-scenes production, and, of course, the pop culture inspired by the global fame of K-pop, as evidenced by the global success of Netflix's <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/if-you-loved-kpop-demon-hunters-watch-these-netflix-gems/" target="_blank"><em>KPop Demon Hunters</em></a>. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/best-movies-and-shows-for-fans-of-k-pop/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Affordable American PHEV SUV That Puts Range Anxiety to Rest]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/affordable-american-phev-suv-that-puts-range-anxiety-to-rest/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025_ford_escape_st-line_elite_2.jpg" length="171" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hybrid Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This SUV is the easy PHEV pick if you want zero range-anxiety drama.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Plug-in hybrid <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/tag/suvs/" target="_blank">SUVs and crossovers</a> are way more useful than most people give them credit for. While <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/category/electric-vehicles/" target="_blank">EVs</a> are the flashy new thing, PHEVs fix range anxiety without making you go fully electric.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 15:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/affordable-american-phev-suv-that-puts-range-anxiety-to-rest/</guid></item></channel>
